That you missed a date?
At best he is sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, the thing is arranged with an apology.
Before you have painful explanations, it is useful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
You're borrowing something that doesn't belong to you?
There's nothing more annoying than wanting to take a file, an office tool or the phone and you can't find them anywhere.
Remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk, but she disappeared the next morning?
You happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Don't take anything from your colleagues without asking otherwise they're right to be mad at you for stealing their property.
Don't bring envelopes, post-it in your pocket because it can be annoying that there's no more envelopes and you need them right now.
Are you chatting about the privacy of colleagues?
There are no good ways to stop spreading gossip.
Who did what, with who?
Or why?
Don't tell everyone your information (suppositions) about the privacy of your colleagues!
If a colleague shares his intimate secrets with you, don't abuse his trust!
Bury the shared information in you and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware of it.
Do you declare yourself ill without just cause?
