Cuba still offers a fantasy that is unique in the world and that will be appreciated especially by fans of small trains.
The cane had been re-entered from the extended plantations in the sugar mills on a narrow track by small steam and motor trains.
Their rolling stock has not been renewed for decades, and this is how small locomotives can be seen running, the contemporary of which are not only in museums elsewhere.
Where to direct his steps?
The majority of visitors do not miss the best known places.
So there is no need to write a lot about Varadero or Havana.
Otherwise remember that in the Hemingway property, already mentioned, there is a museum and that whoever loves this writer should not miss the visit.
One of the most picturesque corners of Cuba is the Vi+ales valley to the west of the island.
Exuberant vegetation grows on calcareous soil.
Mogotes, calcareous balloons and rocks ascend in candlelight from the bottom of the valley, and, fertile soil having caught in their bowels, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetal carpet.
The valley is the place where Cuban tobacco of the highest quality is probably cultivated.
You will be able to meet the final form of this product if you visit one of the cigar factories of Havana.
Perhaps someone will find it equally interesting that this is where the Chilean episode of Major Zeman was shot.
Trinidad
An ancient town founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
It was the slave trade and the sugar trade that brought him glory and wealth.
The richness was embodied in the beauty and the town-vitrine character of this small city.
Koloniální španělská architektura,výrazně ovlivněná pozděj
Trinidad, located between the sea and the mountain massif Escambray, is so far away that still in the 1950s of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay away.
We didn't build anything, and that's why we didn't demolish anything either, everyone just had a roof over their heads.
If you have more time than an afternoon in Trinidad, then it is worth visiting interesting places in the surrounding area, such as Playa Ancón beach or the Sucrose Valley.
Then, in the evening, it is customary to go to the Casa de la Música which comes alive after sunset and where the music does not fade until the early morning.
Baracoa
