The government planned to borrow 159.2 billion kroner this year.
As a result of better-than-expected changes in government budget savings, the Department has reduced the planned amount to DKr 152.8 billion.
The debt of the State of the Czech Republic rose towards the end of September to NOK 842.7 billion.
During the nine months of this year it has therefore increased by 40.2 billion kroons.
From June onwards, however, it fell by 13.4 billion kroons.
