Each Czech is responsible for a debt in excess of 84,000 kroons.
Throughout the last year, the State has incurred more than 111 billion crowns in debt.
"For now, it seems that, thanks to a smaller deficit forecast for next year, we could cross the border by only one trillion kroner in 2009.
