But I am not waiting for this change," he said.
Debts grow
The debt of the State consists of the debts of the central government and is generated mainly by the accumulation of deficits in the State budget.
Government debt is financed by treasury bills, annuity securities, direct loans or, for example, by loans from the European Investment Bank.
The State's internal debt has increased this year from $38.5 billion to NOK 719.4 billion.
The State's external debt has increased this year from DKr 1.7 billion to DKr 123.3 billion.
