What assurance does it suit me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expense which will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, length of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
It is that, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más dificil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is evidenced by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium awarded and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which takes into account various factors, such as age, gender, length of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, by using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency and thus the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver has to study the situation carefully to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
The most significant variables are presented here when choosing one or other type of insurance, so that the insurance company, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of disadvantages when entering into an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and seniority of a driver's licence.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is insurance at all risks, there are other, more cost-effective options.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for any-risk, deductible insurance, so that they get coverage from any-risk insurance but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined by the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," says Luis Noguera, the Spanish manager of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid claims as far as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The subsidies and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses ", clarified Noguera.
After 25 years it becomes easier for drivers when they enter into an insurance contract, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose a risk-free insurance policy.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired in advance after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable for the client to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation permits.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be those with the lowest claim rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be any risk insurance with deductible (up to 300 euros), or a third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have more casual driving and they have more purchasing power to afford the luxury to assume a larger amount of franchises," says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a risk-free insurance policy is preferable (i.e. 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance policy when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a major expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
